      "Based on my search results, I found several **full AI IDEs** and coding editors available in 2026. Here's a comprehensive overview:\n\n## Top AI-Native IDEs in 2026\n\n### 1. **Cursor** ⭐ (Most Popular)\n- **Based on:** VS Code fork, AI-native design\n- **Price:** Free tier / Pro $20/month / Enterprise ~$200/month\n- **Version:** v0.45.0 (stable, released February 2026)\n- **Key Features:** \n  - Natural language code generation\n  - One-click bug fixing\n  - Cross-file project understanding\n  - Composer multi-file editing mode\n- **Best for:** Full-stack development, heavy AI users, beginners\n- **User Rating:** 4.9/5\n\n### 2. **Windsurf** (by Codeium)\n- **Price:** $15/month (subscription)\n- **Key Features:**\n  - Cascade agent mode with strong autonomy\n  - Deep context understanding\n  - Advanced agent capabilities\n- **Best for:** Complex task automation, users who prefer hands-off AI coding\n\n### 3. **GitHub Copilot Workspace** (Microsoft)\n- **Version:** January 2026 update\n- **Price:** $10/month\n- **Key Features:**\n  - Full project generation\n  - Automatic Git integration\n  - Multi-agent collaboration\n  - Supports 1 million token context\n- **Best for:** Team development, enterprise users, GitHub ecosystem\n\n### 4. **Claude Code** (Anthropic)\n- **Price:** Pay-per-token usage\n- **Key Features:**\n  - Terminal-based AI agent\n  - Strong code understanding capabilities\n  - Execute commands, read/write files, Git operations\n- **Best for:** Teams pursuing high code quality\n\n### 5. **Trae** (ByteDance - China)\n- **Price:** Free\n- **Key Features:**\n  - Built on Doubao 1.5-Pro model\n  - Chinese-optimized commands\n  - Chat mode for codebase analysis\n  - Builder mode for app generation\n- **Best for:** Chinese developers, budget-conscious users\n\n### 6. **JetBrains AI Assistant**\n- **Version:** 253.30387.147 (2026)\n- **Key Features:**\n  - Native integration with PyCharm/IDEA\n  - Code completion, refactoring\n  - Unit test generation\n  - Claude 3.7 integration\n- **Best for:** Java/Python backend developers\n\n### Other Notable Mentions:\n- **Zed**: High-performance Rust-written IDE with real-time collaboration\n- **PearAI**: Open-source Cursor alternative with multi-model support\n- **Void**, **Qoder**, **Melty**, **Kiro**: Various specialized AI coding environments\n\n## 2026 AI Coding Trends:\nThe landscape has evolved from terminal-based tools (2025) to comprehensive platforms offering **terminal + IDE + Web + Desktop** experiences. The focus has shifted toward:\n- **Specification-driven development**\n- **Agentic workflows** (Plan → Code → Verify)\n- **Multi-agent collaboration**\n- **Repository-level context understanding**\n\nWould you like more detailed information about any specific AI IDE from this list?"
