tails/146562059\"},{\"title\":\"Ghostwriter-AI\",\"url\":\"https://learn.microsoft.com/zh-cn/microsoft-365-app-certification/word/ghostwriter-ai-legal?pivots=general\"},{\"title\":\"ghostwriter\",\"url\":\"https://m.cidianbao.com/yinghan/uwrcs4a.html\"},{\"title\":\"Ghostwriter\",\"url\":\"https://baike.baidu.com/item/Ghostwriter/5778024\"},{\"title\":\"writer\",\"url\":\"http://mbq.kongfz.com/detail_338939_2_0/\"}]\n\nBased on my web search, I found several AI coding IDE/agent tools that had launch announcements around February 2025:\n\n## Major AI Coding IDE/Agent Launches in February 2025\n\n### 1. **Claude Code by Anthropic** (February 24, 2025)\n- **Launch Date**: February 24, 2025\n- **Type**: Terminal-based \"agentic coding\" tool\n- **Key Features**:\n  - Integrates Claude Opus 4 / Sonnet 4 directly into local terminal and IDE\n  - Automatically parses codebases at scale (multi-million line projects)\n  - Can execute Shell commands, Git operations, and tests with user authorization\n  - Deep code awareness through \"agentic search\"\n  - Multi-file consistent editing across modules\n  - Security controls with confirmations before file modifications\n- **Availability**: Launched as research preview in February 2025, GA on May 23, 2025\n- **Source**: Mentioned as the second item in Claude 3.7 Sonnet announcement\n\n### 2. **GitHub Copilot \"Agent Mode\"** (Early February 2025)\n- **Launch Date**: Early February 2025\n- **Type**: New agentic mode for GitHub Copilot\n- **Key Features**:\n  - Can iterate on its own output\n  - Automatically recognizes and corrects errors\n  - Solves problems autonomously within the IDE\n  - Builds solutions and iterates until correct\n- **Significance**: Represented a major evolution in agentic coding capabilities\n\n### 3. **Replit Ghostwriter Chat** (January 2025, referenced in February discussions)\n- **Launch Date**: January 2025\n- **Type**: Conversational AI programmer integrated into online IDE\n- **Note**: While technically launched in January 2025, it was frequently cited in February 2025 roundups as one of the first conversational AI programmers integrated into an online IDE\n\n---\n\nThese launches collectively marked a significant shift toward \"agentic\" AI coding tools—systems that can autonomously plan, execute, and iterate on complex coding tasks rather than just providing code suggestions or chat responses.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
