 programming with cross-editor collaboration\n  - Natural language IDE\n\n### **Claude Code Neovim Plugin (Recent)**\n- **claudecode.nvim** provides Claude Code AI assistant integration for Neovim\n- Uses WebSocket protocol compatible with MCP protocol\n- Offers seamless migration from VS Code to Neovim\n- Provides similar AI coding experience to official VS Code and JetBrains plugins\n- Installation via Lazy.nvim, Packer, or manual clone\n\n### **Popular AI Coding Tools Overview (February 2026)**\nMainstream AI programming tools supporting these editors:\n\n**For VS Code, JetBrains, and Neovim:**\n- **GitHub Copilot** - Most mature ecosystem, supports 37+ languages, $10/month Pro version\n- **JetBrains AI Assistant** - Native integration for JetBrains IDEs\n- **Tabnine** and **Amazon Q** as alternatives\n\n### **Notable Neovim AI Plugins:**\n- **copilot.vim** / **copilot.lua** - GitHub Copilot integration\n- **codecompanion.nvim** - AI-powered coding\n- **avante.nvim** - Emulates Cursor AI IDE behavior\n- **ai.vim** - OpenAI and GPT integration\n- **vim-ai** - OpenAI and ChatGPT plugin\n\n### **Historical Context**\nGitHub Copilot expanded support to JetBrains IDEs (IntelliJ IDEA, PyCharm) and Neovim in November 2021.\n\n---\n\n**Note:** The search didn't reveal a specific \"launch\" of a new AI extension/plugin specifically in February 2026, but it shows the ongoing evolution and expansion of AI coding tools across all three platforms (VS Code, JetBrains, Neovim) with continued development and integration throughout early 2026.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
